[normal]provided
[normal] as Appendix 1
[normal])
[normal]. The letter
[normal] did not address the need for joined up policy, demonstrated the still very low level of maintenance funding for the 98% of the road network and the lack of recognition that road building wouldn’t solve congestion problems
[normal].
[normal] It recognised that local authori
[normal]ties do generally understand better the local transport issues; however pronouncements by government on parking
[normal] and traffic enforcement
[normal] and control by the DfT 
[normal]and DCLG 
[normal]of minutiae seem to contradict this.
